"from\": 584, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay tuned for live updates across the morning session.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"GermanLeo Neugebauerthrew 53.33m on his first attempt not far off the Olympic Decathlon Best 53.79m that Bryan Clay threw in 2008.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 855, \"end\": 872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Decathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympic Decathlon\", \"types\": [\"Q7889\", \"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Decathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Decathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryan Clay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryan_Clay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neugebauer took over the overall lead again.\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\", \"score\": 0.9981851851898194, \"rank\": 0.001818114351172567, \"text\": \"Neugebauer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shortly after,Lindon Victorof Grenada one-upped Neugebauer and beat the Olympic Best with a thrown of 53.91m, moving him from 10th to fourth in the overall decathlon standings.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.4435868316357315e-22, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"score\": 0.9999961308001095, \"rank\": 3.869214935353222e-06, \"text\": \"Grenada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\"}, {\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\", \"score\": 0.9981851851898194, \"rank\": 0.001818114351172567, \"text\": \"Neugebauer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Otto_E._Neugebauer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's 100m is underway.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With eight heats in total, the first three in each heat and the next three fastest time advance to the Semi-Final.\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Heat 1, Jamaica'sKishane Thompsonran away with an easy 10:00, seemingly shutting it down 50 meters into the race.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9685531298633235e-15, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson is the world leader (9.77) in the event this year.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9575913833787478, \"rank\": 0.044286756486131944, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jeremiah Azu of Great Britain was disqualified for a false start.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1461, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\", \"score\": 0.9999990537371489, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jeremiah Azu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremiah_Azu\"}, {\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999917126843, \"rank\": 8.278967058956848e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Heat 2,Ferdinand Omanyalaof Kenya claimed the win in 10.08  In a Heat 3 shocker, NCAA 100m championLouie Hinchliffe(9.98) of Great Britain took down AmericanNoah Lyles(10.04).\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9997247006258493, \"rank\": 0.00018031521300382715, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8226595476309666e-12, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999917126843, \"rank\": 8.278967058956848e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hinchliffe's effort likely forced Lyles to push longer than he anticipated before shutting it down to take second.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9031835587462211, \"rank\": 0.10719410986769226, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles admitted in his post-race interview with NBC that he downplayed his competitors but stated that will not happen again.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9973741432406533, \"rank\": 0.002615847507581666, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica'sOblique Sevilleran a solid 9.99 in Heat 4 to cruise into the Semi-Final Round.\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Lyles, defending Olympic championMarcell Jacobsof Italy was bested by an NCAA star.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2092, \"end\": 2097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9005545189977036, \"rank\": 0.10661062196203276, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8226595476309666e-12, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NigerianKayinsola Ajayiwon Heat 5 in 10.02 followed by Jacobs in 10.05.\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ajayi finished third in the men's 100m at the 2024 NCAA Division I Outdoor Championships, competing for Auburn University.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2302, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auburn_University\", \"score\": 0.7315474564554512, \"rank\": 0.2415311071318086, \"text\": \"Auburn University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auburn_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Auburn_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jacobs had to battle all the way to the finish line to take second in the heat.\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Heat 6,South Africa'sAkani Simbine (10:03) took down Jamaica'sAckeem Blake(10:06), who finished second.\", \"from\": 2402, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Blake had a good start with a powerful first step putting Simbine under early pressure, but Simbine turned up to a higher gear to break the tape in first place.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"AmericanKenny Bednarekdropped a 9.97 for the fastest time in the round to win Heat 7.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending Olympic 200m champAndre de Grasseof Canada took third (10.07).\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2803, \"end\": 2809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9968804313453512, \"rank\": 0.0030875744113534375, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AmericanFred Kerleymatched his teammate's round best performance of 9.97 in Heat 8 for an easy win over Botswana'sLetsile Tebogo(10.01) and Great Britain'sZharnel Hughes(10.03).\", \"from\": 2831, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2971, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999917126843, \"rank\": 8.278967058956848e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2994, \"end\": 3000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9483479745789828, \"rank\": 0.05381924874685476, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The inaugural Women's 800m Repechage Round gives athletes a second chance at qualifying for the Semi-Final.\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the four-heat round, the first place winner in each heat and next two fastest athletes move on.\", \"from\": 3118, \"to\": 3216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany'sMajtie Kolberg(1.59.08) ran the fastest time.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additional qualifiers were Kenya'sVivian Chebet Kiprotich, France'sAnais Bourgoin,Switzerland's Valentina Rosamilia, Austrailia'sAbbey Caldwell, and Cuba'sRose Mary Almanza.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9997247006258493, \"rank\": 0.00018031521300382715, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3321, \"end\": 3330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiprotich\", \"score\": 0.9999999983465386, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kiprotich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiprotich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiprotich\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AmericanAllie Wilsonran the fifth fastest time in the round but finished third in her heat and did not earn a q. Wilson missed advancing by .08 seconds.\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3561, \"end\": 3567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"score\": 0.5313292748583864, \"rank\": 0.8107833763459955, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/C._J._Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American Harrison Williams threw a Season Best 46.91 to finish second in the Group.\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3602, \"end\": 3610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999992187010829, \"rank\": 7.014025163715955e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3611, \"end\": 3628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrison_A._Williams\", \"score\": 0.9999999999340616, \"rank\": 6.594531078577223e-11, \"text\": \"Harrison Williams\", \"types\": [\"